                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1709" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD BIDWELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Camberwell, and am a miller. On the afternoon of Saturday, the 18th of August, about five o'clock, I was in the fair at Camberwell—I felt a tug at my pocket—I turned round im<lb></lb>mediately, and saw the prisoner drop my handkerchief—he was close to me—I gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I saw it lying on the ground—the gentleman took hold of me. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. I saw it drop from his hand, and picked it up myself.</p>
